,Recommended,224460,32008655,Posted: 27 May,all,Thomas.j.hartnett,"Gorgeous artwork, inventive gameplay, an engaging storyline - and did I mention how exquisite the artwork is? It's not a terribly complex game - once you get a feel for how the puzzles go, you will find yourself able to move from location to location pretty quickly - but there's just enough variety here to keep things from getting rote and boring. The final act was surprisingly moving.One word of caution - because of the mechanics of moving between the physical world and the shadows, and teh trickiness of a handful of the jumps and maneuvers one must make to complete certain puzzles, a game controller is strongly recommended. I was stuck at one point fairly early in the game while playing with mouse and keyboard, but once I played with a controller I was able to progress with ease."
