,Recommended,224460,8894020,"Posted: 28 January, 2014",all,Shadow Hugger,"Puzzle-Platforming, Film Noir Style.Contrastis certainly not for action junkies, nor for gamers who aren't all that interested in storytelling, but for me this little gem from Compulsive Games makes for an excellent puzzle-platformer.The big mechanic here is the ability to shift into silhouette form and solve problems with shadows.  It's remarkably adept at holding player interest becauseContrastgives us so much to do, from simple platforming to complex object manipulation.  The 3D platforming elements are minimal, though there is a fair bit of 2D-3D shifting in certain sections to keep players on their toes.Our intrepid developers have done very well with the Unreal Engine, bringing a dreamscape 1920s world to life with a unique art style that makes full use of a specially commissioned Jazz n' Blues soundtrack.  This game treats us the way a lot of independent titles should: like intelligent people who don't need a compass pointing towards every objective, or a full explanation for every plot point.It isn'tBraidorPortalby any stretch of the imagination, but it is an indie game that has been built with careful attention to detail and a clear love for simple ideas that lead into complexity.  A potential downside is that it's too short.  That said, I paid full price for the Special Edition and I'm not regretting it.So, action-seekers stay away.  Thoughtful types who enjoy their puzzles with a twist of atmosphere - welcome!Still not sure which way you're swinging?  Watch my full video review here:http://store.steampowered.com"
