76561198099446362,Recommended,224460,14746297,"Posted: 5 March, 2015",all,Muze,"This game had so much potential, but ultimately I was disappointed by it. With more work, this could have been a great game.Contrast is a game with a novel mechanic: the player moves between a 3D normal world and a 2D ""shadow world"" to solve platform puzzles. It makes for some really challenging puzzles, but unfortunately, this system can be buggy and unwieldy at times, making some of the puzzles much more difficult than necessary.The game took me three hours to finish. It's not a long game, and I feel that is its biggest weakness. It lacks the depth of a truly immersive story. At the end of the game, I was left wanting more. More backstory. More plot. More explanation. More puzzles to solve. I feel like so much more could have been done with this game to give the player a really good story.The story is set in a beautifully-crafted, dark, intriguing noir-20's/30's world with heavy steampunk accents. The level modeling and art are excellent, but the character modeling and voice acting leaves something to be desired. The actors are rather unpassionate and unconvincing.Contrast is a fun little game, and I definitely recommend it. However, I think it could have been so much more, and ultimately I was disappointed by its lack of depth."
