,Recommended,224460,17921523,"Posted: 6 September, 2015",all,<™[-=> Cookiez <=-]™>,"Okay game. Kind of short. 2 hours and I finished it. It's so simple I think I'll just go for the achievements. The story is a bit peculiar. Sometimes, you will be wondering if everything is in Didi's (little girl protagonist) head. You'll be wondering if you are playing Tim Burton's Psychonauts. You might be assuming that Dawn (shadow girl) is actually grown up Didi but the ending may change your mind. The ending is really interesting. The subtle hint with the hand is quite ""Hmmmm"". Multiverses.I would recommend that you get this on sale at a really low price. It's too short and it's not AAA. But it is ingenious.PROS1. Ingenious Use of ShadowsI love the way the shadow world works on the wall. It's different from games such as Soul Reaver where you alternate between dimensions to find missing pieces. Having a flat surface and light creates very interesting situations.2. DashingQuite fun to use. Fast to transverse the map.3. PuzzlesVery nice. Loved the Solarium. Had to pause for a while to think of where to adjust the correct distance and angles to place the gears. Too few puzzles though and most of them weren't much of a challenge.4. Pirate ShipQuite funny5. Princess StoryLoved it, especially the ridiculous commentary when you fall onto the bamboo. Poor Fred.CONS1. Shadows and Rounded Surfaces, CracksBuggy. The shadows don't work well when it come to cracks and rounded surfaces. They tend to throw you out from the shadow world.2. Way Too Short2 hours is way too short. A slight waste of money. I was hoping for at least 10 hours. I was actually expecting Vincenzo's story, Knight's story, the gangster's or Salvo's story and a little more about Didi.3. LuminariesWhat's the point of collecting all the Luminaries again? You only need 2/3 to power up the lights.NEUTRAL1. CollectiblesThe photos and news clippings are a bit ""meh"". They hardly add to the story since the game already tells you about them."
