76561197995669628,Recommended,224460,26253614,"Posted: 27 October, 2016",all,Sorokonojka,"Contrastis a story driven puzzle-platformer game with interesting light mechanics where you manipulate shadows to create a path. Platforming is not very challenging so it feels more like eye-candy game with some casual puzzles. Overall a unique narrative experience that should take you around 3 to 4 hours to complete.There are some minor issues with gameplay and infrequent glitches like getting stuck but overall Contrast left a positive impression because it is such a beautiful gameI am completely in love with the noir & surreal art style design of the stages. Environments are very exaggerated so it looks like you playing inside a dream or fantasy painting. The lack of characters is probably a budget problem but in a way, it complements gloomy atmosphere that I very much enjoy.The story at first seems very down to earth but the ending kinda puzzled me in a good way. You actually use cutscenes as a platforming objects which is a cool way to tell a story.Despite the weird nature of this game, it is not a hard game to play. Perhaps it depends on a person but I had no problems getting in and out of shadows when It was needed. There were few moments where it was a bit junky and I plummeted to my death but checkpoints are very close so it was not a big issue.Perhaps my only serious problem with the game is the lack of music during puzzle sections. Contrast has some good music but it goes silent during most areas where you stay for 10-20 minutes. Maybe it is a design choice but I really hate doing puzzles with nothing playing in the background.I beat this game just under 4 hours but the quality of the stages justifies the relatively short game. Also, I will play it at least one more time just to collect all the clues but replay value is only held by the art style.Verdict 8/10Not every platforming game needs to be hard or complex. Contrast was relaxing and enjoyable experience even if gameplay felt slightly lacking. It may feel a bit empty when there is no music during puzzles. However Contrast's artistic vision and compelling storytelling were worth my time."
