,Recommended,224460,12520332,"Posted: 16 October, 2014",all,Janos,"Long story short: This game is awesome. I, as a player, had a great time playing it. i enjoyed it, and don't regret for a single moment to have bought it. However for the purpouse of enlighting prospective buyers i will list the pros and cons:PROS:-AWESOME VISUALSi can't understate this enough. The kind of visuals that Tim Burton pioneered before he became a parody of himself. The music is the best the period has to offer. The world is abstract and yet historically accurate. The game portrays the feeling of the 20's like i've never seen before in fiction but also strangely a familiar, timeless story, perfectly relatable to the average player.-The story is extremely engaging, interesting and believable despite the fantastic aspects of the game. You will love the characters, you will care and worry about them if they fall, and will feel a legitimately warm, fuzzy feeling if they succeed. The voice acting is also great, for all the characters wich are written in a way that, again, will make you remember them for a long time. Of special note is Didi: avoiding spoilers i can say that while children are hard to portray in fiction, both in building character and acting, they tend to be hit or miss (think Anakin Skywalker), she is not only very well acted but also very well written, being believable, helpful, and never annoying.- The gameplay is great fun, engaging, the game mechanics are well developed, explained and exploited, making it fun and original, ESPECIALLY if you're a fan of old school plataformers.CONS:-THE GAME IS SHORT. Is that simple. The collectables, tell a great story and are really cool, but they are easy to find in a single playthrough. The world is beautiful and intriguing but the game has a short lifespan, with no replay value whatsoever.-On the gameplay point of view, the save system is kinda arbitrary. There are checkpoints wich work also as autosaves but there's no way of manually save the game, so it can be annoying if you wanna leave inmediatly and you're in the middle of a puzzle, but it is barely noticeable.Veredict:TOTALLY WORTH PLAYING, that being said, if you're strict on your wallet, and wanna make every single cent in it count, it would be wiser to wait until its lower than full price (a 25% discount would be spot on). But considering that is an indie game, made by a developer that is obviously on a budget i think the game deserves the price tag.I hope this review has been useful :D"
