,Recommended,224460,11694050,"Posted: 13 August, 2014",all,Serp,"PROS:Story - the writing and voice acting in this game were greatNovelty - introduction of an innovative game mechanic that lends itself well to creative and challenging puzzlesCONS:Controls - movement is awkward and occasionally a bit frustratingUnpredictable triggers - Use key on the wrong item and you will be taken to the next part of the story before you've had a chance to try and find everything in the current levelLength/Price ratio - This game is a bit expensive for being so short. Totally worth picking up on sale though.Many people complain about glitches but I didn't see anything too obvious. There are some kind of annoying places where you fall through decorative parts near the edge of the level that look like they should support you, but you'll only notice this if you are off exploring. It won't impede progression through the actual game content.Don't expect this to be game that's going to help hone your precision platformer skills. The controls, collisions, and physics are too wonky for that. The puzzles, story, music, art, writing, etc. however, are all very well done, and very cohesive. Nice little game."
