,Recommended,224460,9090574,"Posted: 13 February, 2014",all,Arachin,"A clever but underachieving adventure / puzzle game elevated at times by an interesting setting and story.For those of you that don't know, your character can blend between 3d person and 2d projected platforming by stepping into the light projected onto walls. Shadows become walls, floors and even lifts to new areas. At its best it feels like a mix of fez and portal, but at its worst the shadow stepping can be awkward and unreliable.The pacing is acceptable and there seem to be multiple ways to approach some puzzles, but there's no serious challenge here.The setting falls somewhere between Bugsy Malone and Alice in Wonderland, but doesn't fully deliver on either. The noir story is a nice touch, but not gritty enough for my tastes, and whilst the worlds warp and float like a fever dream this fact is entirely ignored by the characters. I would not have been shocked to see: ""But it was all a dream. The End""There were some beautiful moments towards the end of the game where a deeper meaning is hinted, but it arrived a little late.If you're curious, pick it up on a good sale day, but you're looking for puzzle, platforming or story, this game hits under average on all accounts. [5.0]"
