,Recommended,224460,16430118,"Posted: 15 June, 2015",all,Cuddles the Dalek,"Upsides to this game:-The music is gorgeous. The Streets, House on Fire, and Kat's Song are my favourite tracks from the soundtrack.-The concept is brilliant. Shifting between 3D and 2D? Love it.-The atmosphere is stunning. You are all alone in your world, invisible, but you see Didi's story going on around you. Did I mention the music?-Exploration is rewarded. Little bits of backstory, easter eggs here and there, but invisible walls ruin that a tad.-The story is a simple, small story involving a young girl and her family. No threat of world domination, extinction, etc. Just a little girl who wants her family to be together. It's very touching, and all the more powerful because you can only watch from the sidelines, seeing their silhouettes act out the drama.Downsides to this game:-The puzzles can require spot-on timing and aiming.-The camera and controls can feel awkward.-It's very short. I played through it twice to 100% in just a few hours. A little pricey for the length, but if it's on sale, grab it (the soundtrack too)-Didi can be a little annoying at times.TL;DR (you lazy bugger you):Short with a few annoyances, but the atmosphere and story are amazing, and far outweigh the bad. Get it and the soundtrack when it's on sale."
