,Recommended,224460,13174869,"Posted: 30 November, 2014",all,chigangrel,"8/10Cool game with pretty graphics, great and atmospheric music, a unique gameplay mechanic making for fun puzzles, and a neat little story. Only rating it an 8/10 however because of bugs and other issues (note: my computer exceeds the recommended requirements and played the game fine on high settings). At times, Dawn will slide around at high speeds or suddenly stop moving due to some invisible obstruction. That's annoying while walking down the middle of the road, but downright frustrating when trying to solve puzzles, especially while in shadowland. These movements sometimes cause Dawn to shift out of shadows at inopportune times as well, requiring restarting entire puzzles. The worst issue, however, are the occasional times when something that is supposed to sparkle (such as an item that can be used or a collectible) does NOT sparkle, and thus can't be used. Collectibles don't stop you from completing the game, but the usable items not sparkling certainly will. I was able to solve this issue by restarting the game, but it's still annoying and meant lost progress.All in all though, I would still recommend Contrast."
,Not Recommended,224460,13176713,"Posted: 30 November, 2014",all,roselius,"Though visually stunning and in employ of a very interesting game mechanic I'd never seen before-- the manipulation of lights in order to traverse through a shadow-world to allow the player access to areas that are otherwise unreachable,-- I felt that these two points were not enough to make up for the amount of glitches and the weak plot that I found in an otherwise palatable game. For the amount I bought it for, I felt this game was not polished very well, and it certainly doesn't help that the secondary character you follow was written in a very annoying manner. Noir games are often hit-or-miss because of the amount of stereotypes the genre builds upon, and Contrast followed the routine noir atmosphere and plotline.In short, this was a very imaginative game, but I don't see myself going back to it for another playthrough. I would recommend it for the shadow/light manipulation, however."
