,Recommended,224460,11090073,"Posted: 5 July, 2014",all,fraterormus,"A dark noir atmospheric tale set in the 1920s that is reminiscent of the Dark Horse graphic novel ""Misty Circus"" or many other tales of this genre inspired by Neil Gaiman or the ""Beautiful Stories for Ugly Children"" series. Every aspect about the game is wonderfully enchanting, from the sad storyline of a broken family and child neglect, the beautifully rendered graphics, to the melodic soundtrack. This game successfully transports you to and immerses you in a world of wonder.The mechanics are simple, crossing between a 3d world to a 2d platformer by using light and shadows. The puzzles aren't overly challenging, and neither is the platforming, nor is it necessarily a walk in the park. It's challenging enough to make you feel proud of yourself when you quicly come up with a solution, but not so challenging that you ever get frustrated.Many complaints about this game stem from there not being a tutorial, which IMHO would have ruined the allure of exploring a unqiue world. The only other complaints others have voiced is about bugs which must have been fixed because my playthrough was flawless and entirely bug-free. Pesonally, the only complaint I had about the game is that it is too short and left me wanting more!A word of warning: It can get a little dusty if you take the time to examine the collectibles in the game which may threaten your FPS machismo. You may want to keep your handkerchief nearby if you do."
