,Recommended,224460,16519737,"Posted: 19 June, 2015",all,Naz,"Contrast is a linear game, with lots of platforming and puzzle elements that tie together very well with your shadow shifting abilities. If you're looking for a game with great story that you can just sit and finish in 3-4 hours, this is the game for you.The game is so pretty. The noir style art work is great and ties in really well with the story and setting. The world design is fantastic. If you prefer to take your time, take some screenshots, there's plenty to see. The story is so well written with a surprising ending as well as a hidden storyline that hints at past events. The most interesting part of the game, in my opinion, was the fact that everyone is a shadow. You never see their faces, only Didi's who is the main character. You can't interact with any character directly, yet you can manipulate their shadows to help you achieve objectives. All that has made for a wonderfully atmospheric game that you can really immerse yourself in.On the downside, if you're looking for a game you can play over and over again, skip this game. It's a sit through and play once type of thing. Also, controller highly recommended."
