,Recommended,224460,16505370,"Posted: 18 June, 2015",all,Jericho East,"The pros:- The story is fantastic, and the voice acting is well done. The main character, Didi, is particularly good considering her age- The music creates a wonderful atmosphere, and the world is creatively put together. There are fascinating details throughout, that make you want to explore every nook and cranny- The platforming is clever, and for the most part the mechanics work. A few hiccups here and there, but usually there are work-arounds if you're patient enoughThe cons:- It doesn't say a controller is mandatory, but it should. You should be able to get through the first Act with just a mouse and keyboard, but after that it becomes more challenging. A controller will give you the freedom to maneuver that you're looking for.- Exploration is all but banned. Step too far to get a good look at something and a solid road may actually cause you to fall through the world. There's a lot of hand-holding, particularly in the quest objective that you can never remove from the screen. This is a pity, because it's tempting to take a lot of beautiful screenshots, but you can't without ""Follow Didi"" and ""Go back and meet Didi"" being scrawled on the upper right-hand side almost constantly.- There are few save points, no checkpoints, and no manual saves. This means that if you break a puzzle (it's possible) then resetting from the last save may put you behind a couple hours' worth of work, forcing you to do conquered puzzles over again.Overall, though, this very a very good game and very imaginative. Since the developers plan to make another game (though not a sequel) it will be interesting to see what they have in store."
,Recommended,224460,8263951,"Posted: 24 December, 2013",all,luckydog32,"Contrast has you swapping between 2d and 3d platforming on the fly as your character has the ability to meld into walls with high ""contrast"" lighting. Shadows become navigable platforms that allow you to reach places other wise inaccesible. As you can imagine this creates some interesting puzzles involving moving objects around in 3d space to create your own path way from shadows. The puzzles throw a few monkey wrenches in to try to keep the mechanic from getting stale, but cant maintain the same sense of accomplishment in discovering new way of thinking for the entire 4-5 hour experience.The story does a good job at keeping you interested in the game. You follow a girl and her ""imaginary"" friend as they try to piece together her parents failing relationship. It takes a bit of a weird turn towards the end but it doesn't ruin the rest of the game.It's worth a look if your into platformers at all. Even with the market seemingly flooded with them this one has enough original ideas to float above the rest."
