76561198124965595,Recommended,224460,25729246,"Posted: 27 September, 2016",all,Ayn,"The style of Contrast is right up my ally - it's beautiful, mysterious, slightly eerie and reminiscent of Ye Olden Times romanticism. That combined with the amazingly original premise of playing as an imaginary friend accompaning a little girl living in a world of shadow people made the game a really unique experience. There's something infinitely thrilling in running along the walls as a shadow, climbing on the shadows of others.Unfortunately, that's where it stopped for me, but it could well be that I want this game to be something that it's just not. It's essentially a puzzle game, but I personally found that most of the ""puzzles"" were incredibly easy to solve and the story itself, as much as there was one, was pretty linear, complete with average-to-poor voice acting, thus leaving me wanting more. The full price of Contrast isn't much, but I still have to say that there isn't much content even for that price point - I completed the game in a bit over 3 hours, and that already included several re-dos of some of the sections. I imagine that if one is not as tippy-tumbles as I was, the game is easily completable in 2,5 hours.Don't get me wrong - I still recommend it (especially when it's on sale) to people who like puzzle games for it has a truly unique style, but I personally just feel like the idea of this game has such potential that it's almost kind of wasted here and I would have loved to see it developed to a full-length game with a bit more depth.All 'n' all a solid 7/10  for what it is, 5/10 for what I wish it would be."
76561197969252059,Recommended,224460,31202905,Posted: 17 April,all,Bingo,beautiful game with simple story. the soundtrack is excellent
76561198088542964,Recommended,224460,30351734,Posted: 5 March,all,mdvdb9412,"A fun platformer/puzzle game with a pretty intriguing story. While the story is quite confusing for the first 2/3 of the game, it all gets tied together really nicely at the end. I was glad for that as there were several confusing moments when things just didn't make any sense. If you are caught up on the story, keep playing as it is a really cool concept once you understand the whole plot (for which the collectibles are extremely important, mind you). In addition, the music was quite enjoyable.The puzzles themselves are not too difficult and you can easily grasp what you are supposed to do. The platforming, on the other hand, honestly needs a bit of work (It is at this point I should note I played with the steam controller, so I did not have the problems with the keyboard/mouse controls that some other people were having). The mechanic the game is centered around, transforming into shadow and back is quite unreliable. In fact, once I re-watched the game trailer after finishing the game, I almost had to laugh at the smoothness at which the protagonist was able to switch between the two forms and move about with ease. The unreliability I experienced was  of three forms:1) Sometimes when I wanted to switch to shadow form in the air (next to a wall when the prompt was showing), I was unable to.2) Jump heights of certain platforming areas were off. In more detail, I am specifically speaking about the times where I was not in charge of shaping the jump heights, but rather the ones put in place by the devs that are immovable. I found myself have to repeatedly jump at an obstacle mashing the jump button until my character decided to stick the landing and allow me to rapidly jump up the rest of the obstacle.3) The worst of the three issues is when trying to accomplish some platforming while in shadow form.I found that sometimes I would be forced out of a wall when there were no shadows blocking my path or any other apparent obstacles. Most of the time this would happen on an uneven wall (see Act 3 in the lab for reference) as I was moving forward. For some reason the game does not like the uneven walls and glitches you out of them. This is more ok than the other times it happened (explained next) as it was predictable and something I could plan for. The second way this happened was completely random. I remember most vividly this happening in the scene with the carousel where I would shadow dash through a small obstacle, be clear on the other side but then all of the sudden be forced out of the wall, causing me to need to restart the platforming once again. This happened at random and was quite frustrating to deal with at times.Even with these platforming issues, I feel I must still recommend this game, though not for the price it is offered. I think I got this on sale for $5, which is closer to what I would recommend purchasing it for. I finished the game easily in 3 hours, and even almost 100% on the first run through, only needing about five minutes extra to go back and finish the last two achievements I missed. $10 for 3 hours of gameplay is a little much in my opinion so I would recommend grabbing it while it is on sale.Again, overall, great story and music. The platforming can be a bit frustrating at times, but overall does not detract too much from the gameplay."
